        "comment_id": 61786834
    }],
    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/88f7ca3d3af78cc338fec2e0249668ea?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 465230,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 869184,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/869184/ilya",
                "reputation": 23345,
                "display_name": "Ilya",
                "accept_rate": 40
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 19,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1526315401,
            "creation_date": 1461766610,
            "body": "<p>You can get an iterator from a stream and then wrap the iterator into a <code>Sequence<\/code>:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Sequence { stream.iterator() }\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p><strong>UPD:<\/strong> Starting from Kotlin 1.1 you can use <code>Stream.asSequence()<\/code> extension (see <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/47889522/869184\">Michael Richardson's answer<\/a>), which does the exact same thing as above. The extension is also available for the specialized streams: <code>IntStream<\/code>, <code>LongStream<\/code> and <code>DoubleStream<\/code>.<\/p>\n\n<p>It is located in <code>kotlin.streams<\/code> package in <code>kotlin-stdlib-jdk8<\/code> library (Kotlin 1.2 and above) or in <code>kotlin-stdlib-jre8<\/code> library (Kotlin 1.1 only, deprecated in Kotlin 1.2 and above).<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 36892511,
            "question_id": 36892291,
            "community_owned_date": 1526315401,
            "last_edit_date": 1526315401
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/80317ec9933567081cdc1dc48f5c6a8c?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 2028037,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1812515,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1812515/michael-richardson",
                "reputation": 4312,
                "display_name": "Michael Richardson",
                "accept_rate": 92
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 11,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1524781344,
            "creation_date": 1513695037,
            "body": "<p>Kotlin has an extension method <a href=\"https://kotlinlang.org/api/latest/jvm/stdlib/kotlin.streams/java.util.stream.-stream/as-sequence.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>asSequence()<\/code><\/a> to convert a Java stream to a Kotlin Sequence. In my experience it was not discoverable until I added an import statement:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<pre><code>import kotlin.streams.*\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Then simply use as expected:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<pre><code>val seq = stream.asSequence()\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 47889522,
            "question_id": 36892291,
            "last_edit_date": 1524781344
        }
    ],
